<h3 id="Pull-Mode---No-Routing"><span id="UnifiedAdminGuide-PullMode-NoRouting"></span>Pull Mode - No Routing
 <i18n-message i18nkey="clipboard.copyLink.label" attribute="description">
  <copy-clipboard class="anchor-copy-button" value="https://docs.expertflow.com/cx/4.4/unified-admin-guide#Pull-Mode---No-Routing">
   <svg role="img" aria-hidden="true" data-component="icon" class="icon icon-link copy-headline-link-icon">
    <use href="/__theme/b_8ca5a7d7-80f3-41c8-bea7-75cce14ad14f/scroll-sites-help-center-theme/41/icons.svg#link"></use>
   </svg>
  </copy-clipboard>
 </i18n-message></h3>
<p>Pull mode allows incoming customer requests to be parked to a List instead of being queued to a queue and available to all List Agents (who are subscribed to the List) to pick and join a conversation.</p>
<div data-component="panel" role="note" data-appearance="success">
 <div class="panel-content">
  <p><strong>Tip</strong></p>
  <ul>
   <li>
    <p>To learn more about Lists and Pull-based Routing, see <a href="/cx/4.4/pull-mode-vs-precision-routing" data-scope="internal">Pull-mode vs Precision Routing</a></p>
   </li>
   <li>
    <p>See <a href="/cx/4.4/agent-guide" data-scope="internal">Agent Guide</a> to see how agents get subscribed to and join Pull-based requests</p>
   </li>
  </ul>
 </div>
</div>
<p>The Lists created from here are mapped to Channels while setting up a channel, with the <strong>Routing Mode</strong> → <strong>Pull</strong>.&nbsp;</p>
<h4 id="Add-Lists"><span id="UnifiedAdminGuide-AddLists"></span>Add Lists
 <i18n-message i18nkey="clipboard.copyLink.label" attribute="description">
